@node Introduction "BeSel - Introduction"
@next Features
@prev Main

  @{b}What is BeSel?@{ub}
  --------------

  BeSel is yet another simple boot selector.

  You can set a script or program to 10 function keys (F1-F10)
  and 4 mouse button combinations. BeSel checks which keys or
  buttons are pressed and executes the corresponding scripts or
  programs. If no configuration file is given, BeSel only sets
  a Shell return code which you can use as you like.

  So, you could use BeSel during boot time to tailor your
  environment to different kinds of needs.

  Because of its simplicity BeSel should run on all Amigas.

@endnode

